<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pogostemon dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Pogostemon dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having lanceolate leaves. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer and tubular calyx, smaller ratio of the length of calyx teeth and calyx tube and longer corolla, filament and style (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Morphological comparison between Pogostemon dielsianus and its morphologically similar species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/548984BD11452551F2B5BF88970362B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" tableUuid="548984BD11452551F2B5BF88970362B9">2</tableCitation>
). In addition, the geographical distribution of these three species is also different in that 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to NW Yunnan, China, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Himalayan regions (Bhutan, India, and SE Xizang, China), and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti, GR" journalOrPublisher="London (Botany)" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="77 - 147" refId="B2" refString="Bhatti, GR, Ingrouille, M, 1997. Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum. London (Botany) 27 (2): 77 - 147" title="Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum." volume="27" year="1997">Bhatti and Ingrouille 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" author="Yao, G" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 67" refId="B28" refString="Yao, G, Deng, YF, Ge, XJ, 2015. A taxonomic revision of Pogostemon (Lamiaceae) from China. Phytotaxa 200 (1): 1 - 67, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" title="A taxonomic revision of Pogostemon (Lamiaceae) from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" volume="200" year="2015">Yao et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yao, G" journalOrPublisher="Re dai ya re dai zhi wu xue bao [Journal of tropical and subtropical botany]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="553 - 555" refId="B27" refString="Yao, G, Ge, XJ, 2018. Pogostemon chinensis (Lamiaceae), a newly recorded species from India. Re dai ya re dai zhi wu xue bao [Journal of tropical and subtropical botany] 26 (5): 553 - 555" title="Pogostemon chinensis (Lamiaceae), a newly recorded species from India." volume="26" year="2018">Yao and Ge 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
