<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dunn, ST" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="153 - 171" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/32409023" refId="B7" refString="Dunn, ST, 1913. Notes on Chinese Labiatae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 8: 153 - 171, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/32409023" title="Notes on Chinese Labiatae." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/32409023" volume="8" year="1913">Dunn (1913)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate a type for the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pogostemon dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Pogostemon dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dunn. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti, GR" journalOrPublisher="London (Botany)" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="77 - 147" refId="B2" refString="Bhatti, GR, Ingrouille, M, 1997. Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum. London (Botany) 27 (2): 77 - 147" title="Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum." volume="27" year="1997">Bhatti and Ingrouille (1997)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the specimen deposited in E and K as holotype and isotype, respectively. In fact, they effectively chose the lectotype for the name and the term
<normalizedToken originalValue="“holotype”">&quot;holotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“isotype”">&quot;isotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
can be corrected as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“lectotype”">&quot;lectotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“isolectotype”">&quot;isolectotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
according to Article 9.10 of the International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B23" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
